Linux Mint 5-minute plan:

1. Change password
    - passwd --> current password --> new password

2. Firewall rules
    - sudo apt install ufw
    - sudo ufw status
    - sudo ufw allow [port] 
    - sudo ufw delete [num]
    - sudo ufw deny [port]

    Inbound: 22
    Outbound: 80, 53, 443

3. Processes 
    - ps aux (screenshot)
    - kill -9 [pid]
   
4. Services 
    - ps -aux | less
    - chkconfig [service] off or --del

5. Users 
    - vipw
    - bin/bash --> bin/nologin
    - faillog -a

6. ssh
    - etc/ssh/ssh.config
        - permitrootlogin --> no
        - allowusers --> users
        
7. Harden --> chrome-extension://oemmndcbldboiebfnladdacbdfmadadm/https://lockdown.ubnetdef.org/resources/BeginnerSecurityGuide.pdf         










    
